00:26:29.426 --> 00:26:33.316
well. And so we're also interested in understanding what dictates

431
00:26:33.316 --> 00:26:37.186
this different degree of penetrance and how can we take advantage of that

432
00:26:37.226 --> 00:26:41.066
to either use that as a assessment for risk and

433
00:26:41.166 --> 00:26:44.766
also as a way to potentially reverse the risk or reduce the

434
00:26:44.806 --> 00:26:46.226
risk for high-risk patients.

435
00:26:48.446 --> 00:26:51.026
Hi, Kara Maxwell from Penn. Very happy that you're here-

