00:28:37.366 --> 00:28:37.706
higher

471
00:28:38.626 --> 00:28:41.886
in the normal mice? Is that enough to cause tumor?

472
00:28:42.556 --> 00:28:42.726
Hmm.

473
00:28:42.986 --> 00:28:44.146
Two questions. Thank you.

474
00:28:44.606 --> 00:28:48.466
Right. So in terms of your first question, what drives the activation of

475
00:28:48.506 --> 00:28:51.356
these transcription factors in the early stage of cancer formation?

476
00:28:52.166 --> 00:28:56.086
I think there are a variety of causes for that, specifically in the context of

477
00:28:56.126 --> 00:29:00.026
AP1, it's been well established that it's a stress responsive

478
00:29:00.106 --> 00:29:03.806
transcription factor. So we think that the oncogenic stress at the beginning of

479
00:29:03.846 --> 00:29:07.666
BRCA1 and p53 laws can induce the AP1 and has

480
00:29:07.686 --> 00:29:11.206
been well documented in many other cancer types, including

